{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"liberating-discerning-wildebeest","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Why\n\n`src/rebar/llm/runner.py` is grandfathered over the 800-LOC module-size soft cap (currently 849 LOC by `wc -l`; pinned at ceiling 850 in `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt`, listed in `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt`, with a remedy row in the `docs/architecture.md` offenders table). This story graduates it off the gate by extracting a cohesive leaf module along an existing call-graph seam.\n\n## Seam\n\n`docs/architecture.md`'s remedy row for `llm/runner.py` names this exact seam: \"extract the anthropic-model construction cluster (`_build_retrying_anthropic_model`, `_local_proxy_bypass_base_url`, the httpx timeout/transport wiring) into a sibling `anthropic_model.py`\". This plan follows that row and **widens it plainly**: the named construction cluster alone is close to the 100-LOC floor, so the extraction also pulls the co-resident provider/model-resolution + cache helpers that the same construction path calls (`_pai_model` + its `_PAI_PROVIDER_PREFIX` map, `_anthropic_cache_settings`, and the `_DIRECT_ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL` / `_LOOPBACK_HOSTS` / `_RETRY_STATUSES` constants). The result is a single \"provider/model resolution + Anthropic model construction\" leaf, and this ticket updates/removes the arch.md row accordingly.\n\n## What moves (locate by NAME on current origin/main)\n\nNew leaf `src/rebar/llm/anthropic_model.py`: `_PAI_PROVIDER_PREFIX`, `_anthropic_cache_settings`, `_DIRECT_ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL`, `_LOOPBACK_HOSTS`, `_local_proxy_bypass_base_url`, `_RETRY_STATUSES`, `_build_retrying_anthropic_model`, `_pai_model`. Heavy libraries (httpx, anthropic, pydantic_ai, tenacity, urllib) stay LAZY in-function imports in the new module, preserving the stdlib-only `import rebar.llm` contract. The leaf imports nothing back from `runner.py`.\n\n## Back-compat\n\n`runner.py` re-imports and re-exports the 5 externally referenced names (`_DIRECT_ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL`, `_anthropic_cache_settings`, `_build_retrying_anthropic_model`, `_local_proxy_bypass_base_url`, `_pai_model`) with `# noqa: F401`, so `rebar.llm.runner.<symbol>` attribute access keeps resolving for the importing/monkeypatching tests. `PydanticAIRunner.run()` keeps calling these by BARE re-exported name so the `monkeypatch.setattr(runner_module, \"_pai_model\", ...)` (and `_anthropic_cache_settings` / `_local_proxy_bypass_base_url` / `_build_retrying_anthropic_model`) seam still works. `import os` becomes unused in `runner.py` after the move and is deleted (ruff F401).\n\n## Nature of change / testing plan\n\nThis is a pure/mechanical refactor: no signature or logic change, symbols moved verbatim. E5 testing-plan is not-applicable — the existing tests are the oracle (`tests/unit/test_transport_retry.py`, `tests/unit/test_llm_timeouts.py`, `tests/unit/test_runner_local_proxy_bypass.py`, `tests/unit/test_pydantic_ai_runner.py`, plus `tests/interfaces/store/test_execution_mode_dispatch.py` and `test_llm_framework.py` which access/monkeypatch the re-exported names).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] New `src/rebar/llm/anthropic_model.py` exists and is in [100, 800] LOC (verify: `wc -l src/rebar/llm/anthropic_model.py`)\n- [ ] `src/rebar/llm/runner.py` is <=800 LOC (verify: `wc -l src/rebar/llm/runner.py`)\n- [ ] Re-exports preserved: `python -c \"import rebar.llm.runner as r; [getattr(r,n) for n in ('_DIRECT_ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL','_anthropic_cache_settings','_build_retrying_anthropic_model','_local_proxy_bypass_base_url','_pai_model')]\"` succeeds\n- [ ] `runner.py` graduated off the gate: its line removed from `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt` and `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt`, and its `docs/architecture.md` offenders-table remedy row deleted\n- [ ] `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py -q` passes (allowlist == computed over-cap set == ceilings keys)\n- [ ] `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_transport_retry.py tests/unit/test_llm_timeouts.py tests/unit/test_runner_local_proxy_bypass.py tests/unit/test_pydantic_ai_runner.py -q` passes\n- [ ] `make lint` reports \"All checks passed!\"","id":"c1f4-4a2f-b879-43db","parent_id":"716f-b917-9fc8-41f5","priority":1,"tags":["module-size"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Split llm/runner.py — extract anthropic-model construction into anthropic_model.py"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784397219121823001,"uuid":"f7b0d793-e931-405d-9e7b-667c4b9b46c6"}